1
00:01:12,865 --> 00:01:16,410
Pull yourself together, Teddy.
Pull yourself together.

2
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:24,502
It's just water.

3
00:01:25,753 --> 00:01:27,671
It's a lot of water.

4
00:01:27,963 --> 00:01:29,006
A lot of...

5
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:34,637
Come on.

6
00:01:58,702 --> 00:02:01,831
- You okay, boss?
- Yeah, I'm fine, I just...

7
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:05,709
I just can't... Can't stomach the water.

8
00:02:09,213 --> 00:02:11,882
- You're my new partner.
- That's right.

9
00:02:12,967 --> 00:02:16,011
Not the best way to meet,
with my head halfway down the toilet.

10
00:02:16,053 --> 00:02:19,098
Doesn't exactly square with
"Teddy Daniels, the man, the legend,"

11
00:02:19,181 --> 00:02:21,642
- I'll give you that.
- The legend?

12
00:02:21,725 --> 00:02:24,395
What the hell you boys smoking
over there in Portland, anyway?

13
00:02:24,478 --> 00:02:27,857
Seattle. I came from
the office in Seattle.

14
00:02:30,568 --> 00:02:32,736
How long you been with the Marshals?

15
00:02:32,820 --> 00:02:34,238
Four years.

16
00:02:35,823 --> 00:02:38,159
So you know how small it is.

17
00:02:38,576 --> 00:02:39,660
Sure.

18
00:02:40,703 --> 00:02:43,664
What about you?
You got a girl? Married?

19
00:02:44,498 --> 00:02:45,749
I was.

20
00:02:57,845 --> 00:02:59,221
She died.

21
00:02:59,847 --> 00:03:03,184
- Jesus. I don't...
- Don't worry about it.

22
00:03:04,226 --> 00:03:07,813
There was a fire at the apartment
building while I was at work.

23
00:03:07,897 --> 00:03:09,607
Four people died.

24
00:03:09,690 --> 00:03:13,569
It was the smoke that got her,
not the fire. See, that's important.

25
00:03:13,611 --> 00:03:15,321
I'm sorry, boss.

26
00:03:15,404 --> 00:03:18,240
Where are my goddamn cigarettes?

27
00:03:18,282 --> 00:03:20,367
Oh, here, have one of mine.

28
00:03:20,451 --> 00:03:23,954
I could've sworn they were
in my jacket before I got on.

29
00:03:24,038 --> 00:03:26,749
Government employees
will rob you blind.

30
00:03:29,210 --> 00:03:30,419
Thanks.

31
00:03:31,462 --> 00:03:34,256
They give you a briefing about
the institution before you left?

32
00:03:34,298 --> 00:03:36,967
All I know is it's a mental hospital.

33
00:03:37,801 --> 00:03:39,386
For the criminally insane.

34
00:03:40,930 --> 00:03:43,140
Well, if it's just folks running
around hearing voices

35
00:03:43,182 --> 00:03:46,644
and chasing after butterflies,
they wouldn't need us.

36
00:03:55,819 --> 00:03:58,656
- Is that where we're headed?
- Yep.

37
00:03:59,156 --> 00:04:01,533
The other side of the island
is rock bluffs

38
00:04:01,617 --> 00:04:04,161
all the way down
to the edge of the water.

39
00:04:04,245 --> 00:04:07,706
The dock, it's the only way on or off.

40
00:04:08,791 --> 00:04:11,794
We'll be casting off
as soon as you two are ashore.

41
00:04:11,835 --> 00:04:14,505
I'd appreciate it if you'd hurry up about it.

42
00:04:14,546 --> 00:04:17,299
- Why?
- Storm's coming.

43
00:04:43,701 --> 00:04:46,328
Never seen a Marshals badge before.

44
00:04:47,997 --> 00:04:49,873
I'm Deputy Warden McPherson,
gentlemen.

45
00:04:49,957 --> 00:04:51,166
Welcome to Shutter Island.

46
00:04:51,208 --> 00:04:54,253
I'll be the one taking you
up to Ashecliffe.

47
00:05:06,557 --> 00:05:09,435
Your boys seem a little on edge,
Mr. McPherson.

48
00:05:09,518 --> 00:05:11,895
Right now, Marshal, we all are.

49
00:05:55,939 --> 00:05:58,192
Electrified perimeter.

50
00:06:00,027 --> 00:06:01,779
How can you tell?

51
00:06:02,112 --> 00:06:04,698
I've seen something like it before.

52
00:06:33,227 --> 00:06:37,147
All right. You gentlemen will be accorded
all the help we can give,

53
00:06:37,231 --> 00:06:40,192
but during your stay,
you will obey protocol.

54
00:06:40,275 --> 00:06:41,652
Is that understood?

55
00:06:41,735 --> 00:06:43,112
Absolutely.

56
00:06:43,570 --> 00:06:46,949
The red brick building on your right
is Ward A, the male ward.

57
00:06:46,990 --> 00:06:50,369
Ward B, the female ward,
is the one on your left.

58
00:06:50,452 --> 00:06:53,414
Ward C is that building on the bluffs.

59
00:06:53,497 --> 00:06:55,124
An old Civil War fort.

60
00:06:55,165 --> 00:06:57,584
The most dangerous patients
are housed there.

61
00:06:57,668 --> 00:06:59,628
Admittance to Ward C is forbidden

62
00:06:59,670 --> 00:07:02,339
without the written consent
and physical presence

63
00:07:02,423 --> 00:07:05,008
of both myself and Dr. Cawley.

64
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:06,844
Is that understood?

65
00:07:07,803 --> 00:07:10,222
You act like insanity is catching.

66
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:16,353
You are hereby required
to surrender your firearms.

67
00:07:17,855 --> 00:07:21,233
Mr. McPherson, we are duly appointed
federal marshals.

68
00:07:21,316 --> 00:07:23,861
We are required to carry our firearms
with us at all times.

69
00:07:23,902 --> 00:07:26,905
Executive order 319
of the Federal Code of Penitentiaries

70
00:07:26,989 --> 00:07:29,032
states that when inside a penitentiary,

71
00:07:29,116 --> 00:07:32,536
the officers of that institution
have final authority.

72
00:07:35,414 --> 00:07:39,418
Gentlemen, you will not get through
this gate with your firearms.

73
00:07:58,854 --> 00:08:02,191
Okay. Now that the official stuff's done,
come on, boys,

74
00:08:02,232 --> 00:08:04,193
what do you say we go find Dr. Cawley?

75
00:08:16,246 --> 00:08:18,916
When did she escape? This prisoner?

76
00:08:18,999 --> 00:08:23,170
I'm afraid Dr. Cawley will have
to fill you in on the situation. Protocol.

77
00:08:23,253 --> 00:08:25,422
Correctional officers
at a mental institution,

78
00:08:25,464 --> 00:08:27,633
that's a weird sight,
if you don't mind me saying.

79
00:08:27,716 --> 00:08:31,136
It's the only facility
of its kind in the U.S., even the world.

80
00:08:31,220 --> 00:08:33,764
We take only the most dangerous,
damaged patients,

81
00:08:33,847 --> 00:08:35,807
ones no other hospital can manage.

82
00:08:35,891 --> 00:08:37,809
And it's all due to Dr. Cawley.

83
00:08:37,893 --> 00:08:39,811
He's created something
really unique here.

84
00:08:39,895 --> 00:08:43,482
It's a hospital for people our society
normally considers beyond treatment.

85
00:09:08,090 --> 00:09:10,050
Top of his class
at Johns Hopkins, then Harvard...

86
00:09:11,468 --> 00:09:13,220
IDs, gentlemen.

87
00:09:16,723 --> 00:09:18,850
Show your badges, gentlemen.

88
00:09:18,934 --> 00:09:22,938
Dr. Cawley's been consulted
numerous times by Scotland Yard,

89
00:09:22,980 --> 00:09:25,440
- MI5, the OSS...
- Why?

90
00:09:26,483 --> 00:09:28,151
What do you mean?

91
00:09:29,486 --> 00:09:32,739
What do intelligence agencies
want to consult a psychiatrist about?

92
00:09:32,823 --> 00:09:35,117
I guess you'll have to ask him.

93
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:47,004
- Marshal Daniels.
- Doctor.

94
00:09:47,462 --> 00:09:49,047
Marshal Aule.

95
00:09:49,506 --> 00:09:52,217
Thank you, Deputy Warden.
That will be all.

96
00:09:52,301 --> 00:09:54,970
Yes, sir. Pleasure, gentlemen.

97
00:09:56,638 --> 00:09:58,348
He had a lot to say about you.

98
00:09:58,390 --> 00:10:01,602
McPherson's a good man.
He believes in the work we do here.

99
00:10:01,685 --> 00:10:04,021
And what would that be, exactly?

100
00:10:04,062 --> 00:10:07,733
A moral fusion between law and order
and clinical care.

101
00:10:07,816 --> 00:10:10,819
Pardon me, Doc.
A what between what and what?

102
00:10:17,784 --> 00:10:20,871
Those paintings are quite accurate.

103
00:10:20,912 --> 00:10:22,831
Used to be the kind of patients
we deal with here

104
00:10:22,873 --> 00:10:26,084
were shackled and left in their own filth.

105
00:10:26,168 --> 00:10:27,461
They were beaten,

106
00:10:27,544 --> 00:10:29,796
as if whipping them bloody
would drive the psychosis out.

107
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:32,007
We drove screws into their brains,

108
00:10:32,049 --> 00:10:35,886
we submerged them in icy water
until they lost consciousness

109
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,430
or even drowned.

110
00:10:38,513 --> 00:10:40,474
- And now?
- We treat them.

111
00:10:40,557 --> 00:10:42,768
Try to heal, try to cure.

112
00:10:42,851 --> 00:10:44,519
And if that fails,
at least we provide them

113
00:10:44,561 --> 00:10:47,856
with a measure of comfort
in their lives. Calm.

114
00:10:47,898 --> 00:10:51,151
These are all violent offenders, right?

115
00:10:51,234 --> 00:10:53,487
I mean, they've hurt people.

116
00:10:54,279 --> 00:10:57,991
- Murdered them in some cases.
- In almost all cases, yes.

117
00:10:58,075 --> 00:10:59,910
Then, personally, Doctor,
I'd have to say,

118
00:10:59,993 --> 00:11:02,371
screw their sense of calm.

119
00:11:03,955 --> 00:11:07,751
It's my job to treat my patients,
not their victims. I'm not here to judge.

120
00:11:07,793 --> 00:11:10,420
- So this female prisoner...
- Patient.

121
00:11:11,254 --> 00:11:13,173
Excuse me. Patient,

122
00:11:13,256 --> 00:11:18,387
one Rachel Solando,
escaped sometime in the last 24 hours.

123
00:11:18,428 --> 00:11:22,349
- Last night between 10:00 and midnight.
- Is she considered dangerous?

124
00:11:22,432 --> 00:11:26,061
You could say that.
She killed all three of her children.

125
00:11:26,978 --> 00:11:29,898
She drowned them in the lake
behind her house.

126
00:11:29,940 --> 00:11:33,276
She took them out one by one,
held their heads under till they died,

127
00:11:33,318 --> 00:11:36,196
then she brought them back inside and
arranged them around the kitchen table.

128
00:11:36,279 --> 00:11:39,616
She ate a meal there
before a neighbor dropped by.

129
00:11:41,576 --> 00:11:42,744
And what about the husband?

130
00:11:42,786 --> 00:11:46,498
He died on the beaches of Normandy.
She's a war widow.

131
00:11:47,124 --> 00:11:49,584
She starved herself
when she first came here.

132
00:11:49,626 --> 00:11:52,462
She insisted the children weren't dead.

133
00:12:02,305 --> 00:12:05,058
Sorry, Doctor. You don't happen
to have an aspirin, do you?

134
00:12:05,142 --> 00:12:07,894
- Prone to headaches, Marshal?
- Sometimes. But today,

135
00:12:07,978 --> 00:12:11,940
- I'm a little more prone to seasickness.
- Ah, dehydration.

136
00:12:12,190 --> 00:12:13,817
- You all right, boss?
- Yeah.

137
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:16,653
In that case, you're quite right.
The simpler the better.

138
00:12:16,695 --> 00:12:18,238
Thanks so much.

139
00:12:19,114 --> 00:12:22,117
Rachel still believes
the children are alive.

140
00:12:22,659 --> 00:12:25,662
She also believes
this place is her home in the Berkshires.

141
00:12:27,706 --> 00:12:30,041
- You're kidding me.
- She's never once in two years

142
00:12:30,125 --> 00:12:31,835
acknowledged that she's
in an institution.

143
00:12:31,877 --> 00:12:35,756
She believes we're all deliverymen,
milkmen, postal workers.

144
00:12:35,839 --> 00:12:38,049
To sustain the delusion
that her children never died,

145
00:12:38,133 --> 00:12:40,177
she's created
an elaborate fictional structure,

146
00:12:40,218 --> 00:12:43,597
and she gives us all
parts to play in that fiction.

147
00:12:44,514 --> 00:12:46,600
So have you searched the grounds yet?

148
00:12:46,683 --> 00:12:49,269
The warden and his men
scoured the island.

149
00:12:49,352 --> 00:12:50,854
Not a trace.

150
00:12:51,438 --> 00:12:56,026
And what's more disturbing is we don't
know how she got out of her room.

151
00:12:56,067 --> 00:12:59,863
It was locked from the outside,
and the only window is barred.

152
00:13:02,699 --> 00:13:06,161
It's as if she evaporated
straight through the walls.

153
00:13:12,042 --> 00:13:15,879
I brought her right back here
after group therapy, locked her in,

154
00:13:15,962 --> 00:13:18,965
came back for midnight rounds,
she was gone.

155
00:13:25,764 --> 00:13:29,976
Seriously, Doctor, how is it possible
that the truth never gets through to her?

156
00:13:30,060 --> 00:13:32,979
I mean,
she's in a mental institution, right?

157
00:13:33,063 --> 00:13:35,065
Seems like something you'd notice
from time to time.

158
00:13:35,148 --> 00:13:37,317
How many pairs of shoes
are the patients given?

159
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:38,777
Two pairs.

160
00:13:38,860 --> 00:13:43,114
Sanity's not a choice, Marshal.
You can't just choose to get over it.

161
00:13:43,698 --> 00:13:47,077
So, she left here barefoot?

162
00:13:47,744 --> 00:13:50,497
Come on, Doc,
she couldn't get 10 yards in that terrain.

163
00:13:51,873 --> 00:13:53,166
Marshal?

164
00:14:12,352 --> 00:14:14,187
This is definitely Rachel's handwriting.

165
00:14:14,271 --> 00:14:17,107
I have no idea
what the law of four is, though.

166
00:14:17,190 --> 00:14:20,068
- It's not a psychiatric term?
- I'm afraid not.

167
00:14:20,110 --> 00:14:21,611
"Who is 67?"

168
00:14:22,863 --> 00:14:23,947
Fuck if I know.

169
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:27,075
I have to say that's quite close
to my clinical conclusion.

170
00:14:27,951 --> 00:14:29,870
Think it's just random scribblings?

171
00:14:29,953 --> 00:14:33,707
Oh, no, not at all. Rachel's smart.
Brilliant, in fact.

172
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:35,250
This paper could be important.

173
00:14:35,292 --> 00:14:38,169
Excuse me, Doctor,
but we're gonna have to hold on to this.

174
00:14:38,253 --> 00:14:39,629
Of course.

175
00:14:41,548 --> 00:14:44,467
And you say
she had to come through here?

176
00:14:44,509 --> 00:14:48,805
After lights out,
the orderlies play cards in here.

177
00:14:48,847 --> 00:14:52,183
Last night, there were seven men
sitting at the base of those stairs

178
00:14:52,267 --> 00:14:53,727
playing stud poker.

179
00:14:53,810 --> 00:14:56,855
Yet somehow,
Rachel managed to slip past them.

180
00:14:57,564 --> 00:14:58,607
Why?

181
00:14:58,648 --> 00:15:01,276
How? She turns invisible?

182
00:15:02,152 --> 00:15:04,279
Doctor, we're gonna need access
to the personnel files

183
00:15:04,321 --> 00:15:05,363
of all the medical staff.

184
00:15:05,447 --> 00:15:08,283
The nurses, the guards, the orderlies,
anyone who was working then.

185
00:15:08,325 --> 00:15:10,493
We'll take your request
under consideration.

186
00:15:10,535 --> 00:15:13,830
This is not a request, Doctor.

187
00:15:13,914 --> 00:15:16,416
This is a federal facility,
and a dangerous prisoner...

188
00:15:16,499 --> 00:15:18,710
- Patient.
- ...patient

189
00:15:18,793 --> 00:15:21,087
has escaped. Now, you will comply or...

190
00:15:21,171 --> 00:15:23,506
All I can say is I'll see what I can do.

191
00:15:23,590 --> 00:15:28,553
Doctor, we're gonna need to speak
with the staff. Do you understand?

192
00:15:28,637 --> 00:15:30,847
I'll assemble them in the common room
after dinner.

193
00:15:31,973 --> 00:15:33,224
<i>If you have any further questions,</i>

194
00:15:33,308 --> 00:15:36,603
<i>feel free to join the deputy warden
in the search.</i>

195
00:15:49,032 --> 00:15:50,575
It's 11 miles
to the nearest land

196
00:15:50,659 --> 00:15:52,369
and the water's freezing.

197
00:15:52,452 --> 00:15:55,538
Current was strong last night,
tide pushing in.

198
00:15:55,580 --> 00:15:57,207
She'd have drowned
or been crushed on the rocks,

199
00:15:57,248 --> 00:16:00,418
and her body would have
washed back up on shore.

200
00:16:03,380 --> 00:16:06,633
What about those caves
down there? Have you checked them?

201
00:16:06,716 --> 00:16:09,094
No way she could get there.

202
00:16:09,177 --> 00:16:11,972
The bases of those cliffs
are covered in poison ivy,

203
00:16:12,055 --> 00:16:16,101
live oak, sumac, a thousand plants
with thorns as big as my dick.

204
00:16:16,893 --> 00:16:20,063
You said yourself, Marshal,
she's got no shoes.

205
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:28,071
All right, let's check the other side.

206
00:16:33,451 --> 00:16:36,413
- What's that tower?
- It's an old lighthouse.

207
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:39,874
The guards already searched inside it.

208
00:16:41,793 --> 00:16:44,004
What's in there? More patients?

209
00:16:44,087 --> 00:16:46,214
Sewage treatment facility.

210
00:16:46,673 --> 00:16:50,593
It's getting dark soon.
I'm calling this off for tonight.

211
00:16:50,677 --> 00:16:52,220
Let's go, boys!

212
00:16:56,099 --> 00:16:58,018
<i>You were on watch
on the landing, huh?</i>

213
00:16:58,101 --> 00:17:01,521
Yeah. Couldn't nobody get in or out
of their room on that corridor

214
00:17:01,604 --> 00:17:03,356
without me seeing.

215
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:08,153
Okay, Rachel Solando, who else
does she have to pass to get down here?

216
00:17:14,367 --> 00:17:17,037
Me. Glen Miga.

217
00:17:18,288 --> 00:17:19,873
Sir, I didn't see nothing.

218
00:17:20,290 --> 00:17:22,292
And you were at your post all night?

219
00:17:22,375 --> 00:17:24,711
Yeah, but I didn't see a thing.

220
00:17:26,713 --> 00:17:27,922
Glen.

221
00:17:29,591 --> 00:17:30,759
Glen.

222
00:17:33,595 --> 00:17:35,346
Tell me the truth.

223
00:17:36,473 --> 00:17:37,766
I...

224
00:17:39,809 --> 00:17:42,062
I maybe went to the bathroom.

225
00:17:42,562 --> 00:17:45,273
What? You breached protocol. Christ...

226
00:17:45,315 --> 00:17:47,650
I wasn't gone more than a minute.

227
00:17:47,734 --> 00:17:50,737
All right, look. Let's back up here.
Let's all just back up.

228
00:17:50,820 --> 00:17:54,240
Miss Solando was put in her room
for lights out.

229
00:17:54,324 --> 00:17:57,786
Does anyone here know
what she did before that?

230
00:17:57,827 --> 00:17:59,537
Anyone?

231
00:18:00,038 --> 00:18:01,122
Come on, anyone, anyone,

232
00:18:01,164 --> 00:18:02,332
anyone, anyone.

233
00:18:03,041 --> 00:18:05,460
She was in a group therapy session.

234
00:18:05,502 --> 00:18:08,338
Huh. Anything unusual occur?

235
00:18:09,506 --> 00:18:11,216
Define "unusual."

236
00:18:11,716 --> 00:18:12,759
Excuse me?

237
00:18:12,842 --> 00:18:17,222
This is a mental institution, Marshal,
for the criminally insane.

238
00:18:17,305 --> 00:18:19,265
Usual isn't a big part of our day.

239
00:18:21,309 --> 00:18:22,936
I will rephrase.

240
00:18:23,019 --> 00:18:26,981
Did anything happen last night
during group therapy that was more,

241
00:18:27,023 --> 00:18:29,526
let's say, I don't know,
memorable than...

242
00:18:29,609 --> 00:18:31,361
- Normal?
- Exactly.

243
00:18:32,112 --> 00:18:33,822
No. Sorry.

244
00:18:34,197 --> 00:18:37,492
Did Miss Solando say anything
during group therapy?

245
00:18:38,368 --> 00:18:40,662
She was worried about the rain.

