- Come on.

988
01:18:15,608 --> 01:18:17,985
Wait, wait, what are we doing?
We got the intake form.

989
01:18:18,069 --> 01:18:19,862
It's proof there's a 67th patient,

990
01:18:19,946 --> 01:18:22,782
which they said, repeatedly,
doesn't exist.

991
01:18:23,241 --> 01:18:26,452
I'm getting to that lighthouse.
You understand?

992
01:18:28,788 --> 01:18:30,498
What the hell can I say to you
to stop you?

993
01:18:30,581 --> 01:18:32,917
Why would you want to, Chuck? Why?

994
01:18:32,959 --> 01:18:34,794
Because climbing down there
when it's dark

995
01:18:34,877 --> 01:18:38,047
is a thin step short of suicide,
that's why.

996
01:18:38,131 --> 01:18:41,551
Okay, maybe you better
sit this one out then.

997
01:18:43,136 --> 01:18:45,138
You brought me into this, boss,

998
01:18:45,221 --> 01:18:48,558
and now we're trapped here on this rock,
on this island,

999
01:18:48,641 --> 01:18:50,184
with no one to rely on but each other,

1000
01:18:50,268 --> 01:18:53,730
- and now you're acting like...
- Like what? Like what?

1001
01:18:54,355 --> 01:18:55,857
How am I acting?

1002
01:19:00,153 --> 01:19:03,614
What the hell happened back there
in those cells, Ted?

1003
01:19:08,327 --> 01:19:11,080
What do you think the weather's like
in Portland, Chuck?

1004
01:19:11,664 --> 01:19:13,332
I'm from Seattle.

1005
01:19:15,960 --> 01:19:17,211
Seattle.

1006
01:19:20,423 --> 01:19:21,674
I'm going on

1007
01:19:22,508 --> 01:19:23,718
alone.

1008
01:19:26,095 --> 01:19:28,973
- I'm going with you, boss.
- I said alone.

1009
01:19:30,683 --> 01:19:31,809
Fine.

1010
01:19:58,461 --> 01:19:59,712
Damn it!

1011
01:20:00,713 --> 01:20:02,006
Damn it.

1012
01:20:07,220 --> 01:20:10,097
I knew it wouldn't take long,
but I couldn't get to it.

1013
01:20:10,181 --> 01:20:11,724
The tide was up.

1014
01:20:19,982 --> 01:20:21,108
Chuck!

1015
01:20:23,653 --> 01:20:24,821
Chuck!

1016
01:21:26,382 --> 01:21:27,633
Come on!

1017
01:22:03,002 --> 01:22:04,170
Chuck!

1018
01:22:04,754 --> 01:22:06,672
Where are you, Chuck?

1019
01:22:31,322 --> 01:22:32,531
Chuck!

1020
01:22:34,241 --> 01:22:35,409
Chuck!

1021
01:23:19,912 --> 01:23:21,288
Who are you?

1022
01:23:23,416 --> 01:23:26,252
I'm Teddy Daniels. I'm a cop.

1023
01:23:27,628 --> 01:23:29,338
You're the marshal.

1024
01:23:30,297 --> 01:23:31,966
That's right.

1025
01:23:34,135 --> 01:23:38,055
Would you mind taking your hand
from behind your back, please?

1026
01:23:38,097 --> 01:23:39,932
Why? Why?

1027
01:23:41,434 --> 01:23:44,437
I wanna make sure that
what you're holding won't hurt me.

1028
01:23:52,111 --> 01:23:53,821
I'm gonna keep this

1029
01:23:55,322 --> 01:23:56,824
if you don't mind.

1030
01:23:57,658 --> 01:23:59,076
Fine by me.

1031
01:24:08,127 --> 01:24:09,462
You're...

1032
01:24:10,880 --> 01:24:12,715
You're Rachel Solando.

1033
01:24:14,300 --> 01:24:15,718
The real one.

1034
01:24:19,722 --> 01:24:21,348
Did you kill your children?

1035
01:24:23,142 --> 01:24:24,977
I never had children.

1036
01:24:25,644 --> 01:24:27,438
I was never married.

1037
01:24:28,981 --> 01:24:32,526
And before I was a patient at Ashecliffe,
I worked here.

1038
01:24:33,152 --> 01:24:35,738
You... You were a nurse?

1039
01:24:38,074 --> 01:24:40,034
I was a doctor, Marshal.

1040
01:24:43,454 --> 01:24:45,164
You think I'm crazy.

1041
01:24:45,539 --> 01:24:48,876
- No. No, no, I never...
- And if I say I'm not crazy?

1042
01:24:50,086 --> 01:24:52,505
Well, that hardly helps, does it?

1043
01:24:53,339 --> 01:24:55,841
That's the Kafkaesque genius of it.

1044
01:24:59,136 --> 01:25:01,430
People tell the world you're crazy,

1045
01:25:01,514 --> 01:25:05,434
and all your protests to the contrary
just confirm what they're saying.

1046
01:25:06,018 --> 01:25:09,188
I'm not following you. I'm sorry.

1047
01:25:09,814 --> 01:25:11,816
Once you're declared insane,

1048
01:25:11,857 --> 01:25:15,361
then anything you do is called
part of that insanity.

1049
01:25:15,444 --> 01:25:21,033
Reasonable protests are denial.
Valid fears, paranoia.

1050
01:25:21,117 --> 01:25:22,701
Survival instincts are

1051
01:25:23,702 --> 01:25:25,162
defense mechanisms.

1052
01:25:25,496 --> 01:25:29,208
You're smarter than you look, Marshal.
That's probably not a good thing.

1053
01:25:30,084 --> 01:25:32,753
- Tell me something.
- Yeah.

1054
01:25:33,921 --> 01:25:35,714
What happened to you?

1055
01:25:36,549 --> 01:25:39,969
I started asking about these
large shipments of sodium amytal

1056
01:25:40,052 --> 01:25:41,846
and opium-based hallucinogens.

1057
01:25:41,887 --> 01:25:43,597
Psychotropic drugs.

1058
01:25:44,974 --> 01:25:47,351
I asked about the surgeries, too.

1059
01:25:49,395 --> 01:25:51,564
You ever heard of
a transorbital lobotomy?

1060
01:25:53,107 --> 01:25:55,860
They zap the patient with electroshock,

1061
01:25:55,901 --> 01:25:58,737
then go through the eye with an ice pick,

1062
01:26:00,906 --> 01:26:02,992
pull out some nerve fibers.

1063
01:26:05,411 --> 01:26:07,913
Makes the patients much more obedient.

1064
01:26:07,955 --> 01:26:09,290
Tractable.

1065
01:26:10,749 --> 01:26:12,251
It's barbaric,

1066
01:26:13,252 --> 01:26:14,753
unconscionable.

1067
01:26:15,754 --> 01:26:19,508
Do you know how pain
enters the body, Marshal? Do you?

1068
01:26:20,759 --> 01:26:22,261
Depends on where you're hurt?

1069
01:26:22,303 --> 01:26:24,847
No, it has nothing to do with the flesh.

1070
01:26:25,264 --> 01:26:27,266
The brain controls pain.

1071
01:26:28,100 --> 01:26:32,479
The brain controls fear, empathy, sleep,
hunger, anger. Everything.

1072
01:26:34,815 --> 01:26:36,609
What if you could control it?

1073
01:26:37,109 --> 01:26:40,112
- You mean the brain?
- Recreate a man

1074
01:26:40,779 --> 01:26:45,367
so he doesn't feel pain or love
or sympathy.

1075
01:26:46,911 --> 01:26:48,412
A man who can't be interrogated,

1076
01:26:48,454 --> 01:26:51,165
because he has no memories
to confess.

1077
01:26:53,751 --> 01:26:57,463
You can never take away
all a man's memories. Never.

1078
01:26:57,504 --> 01:27:01,634
Marshal, the North Koreans
used American POWs

1079
01:27:01,717 --> 01:27:03,427
during their brainwashing experiments.

1080
01:27:03,469 --> 01:27:06,931
They turned soldiers into traitors.
That's what they're doing here.

1081
01:27:06,972 --> 01:27:09,099
They're creating ghosts
to go out in the world

1082
01:27:09,141 --> 01:27:12,394
and do things sane men...
Sane men never would.

1083
01:27:12,478 --> 01:27:15,814
To have that kind of ability,
that kind of knowledge,

1084
01:27:15,898 --> 01:27:18,567
- that would take years.
- Years. Years of research.

1085
01:27:18,651 --> 01:27:21,362
Hundreds of patients to experiment on.

1086
01:27:22,613 --> 01:27:26,575
Fifty years from now, people will
look back and say, here, this place,

1087
01:27:26,909 --> 01:27:29,161
is where it all began.

1088
01:27:29,203 --> 01:27:33,999
The Nazis used the Jews, Soviets used
prisoners in their own Gulags, and we,

1089
01:27:34,833 --> 01:27:38,295
we tested patients on Shutter Island.

1090
01:27:39,964 --> 01:27:41,632
No, they won't.

1091
01:27:42,591 --> 01:27:43,592
No.

1092
01:27:46,053 --> 01:27:48,180
You do understand

1093
01:27:50,724 --> 01:27:53,018
that they can't let you leave.

1094
01:27:53,310 --> 01:27:56,647
I am a federal marshal.
They can't stop me.

1095
01:27:58,023 --> 01:28:03,112
I was an esteemed psychiatrist
from a respected family.

1096
01:28:05,197 --> 01:28:06,824
Didn't matter.

1097
01:28:09,535 --> 01:28:13,580
Let me ask you.
Any past traumas in your life?

1098
01:28:14,957 --> 01:28:16,208
Yes.

1099
01:28:17,376 --> 01:28:19,461
But why would that matter?

1100
01:28:19,545 --> 01:28:21,880
Because they're gonna point
to some event in your past

1101
01:28:21,922 --> 01:28:24,425
and say it's the reason
you lost your sanity.

1102
01:28:24,508 --> 01:28:29,888
So that when they commit you here,
your friends and colleagues will say,

1103
01:28:29,972 --> 01:28:31,890
"Of course he cracked.

1104
01:28:32,891 --> 01:28:34,184
"Who wouldn't
after what he'd been through?"

1105
01:28:34,226 --> 01:28:36,729
They can say that about anyone,
anyone at all.

1106
01:28:36,812 --> 01:28:39,773
The point is
they're gonna say it about you.

1107
01:28:43,027 --> 01:28:46,864
- How's your head?
- My head?

1108
01:28:46,905 --> 01:28:50,326
Any funny dreams lately?
Trouble sleeping?

1109
01:28:52,536 --> 01:28:56,915
- Headaches?
- I am prone to migraines, yes.

1110
01:28:56,957 --> 01:28:58,250
Jesus.

1111
01:29:00,544 --> 01:29:04,089
You haven't taken any pills, have you?
I mean, even aspirin?

1112
01:29:04,131 --> 01:29:06,300
- The aspirin?
- Jesus.

1113
01:29:06,967 --> 01:29:10,679
And you ate the food in the cafeteria
and drank the coffee they gave you?

1114
01:29:10,763 --> 01:29:14,141
You tell me, at least, that you've
been smoking your own cigarettes.

1115
01:29:15,934 --> 01:29:17,144
No.

1116
01:29:18,103 --> 01:29:19,229
No.

1117
01:29:20,314 --> 01:29:21,690
No, I haven't.

1118
01:29:21,774 --> 01:29:24,568
It takes 36 to 48 hours
for neuroleptic narcotics

1119
01:29:24,610 --> 01:29:27,196
to reach workable levels
in the bloodstream.

1120
01:29:28,989 --> 01:29:30,824
Palsy comes first,

1121
01:29:31,742 --> 01:29:35,204
first the fingertips,
then eventually the whole hand.

1122
01:29:36,121 --> 01:29:40,292
Seen any walking nightmares
lately, Marshal? Huh?

1123
01:29:42,795 --> 01:29:45,756
Tell me what goes on in that lighthouse.

1124
01:29:46,632 --> 01:29:47,966
Tell me.

1125
01:29:49,134 --> 01:29:50,761
Brain surgery.

1126
01:29:51,428 --> 01:29:55,891
The let's-open-the-skull-and-see-
what-happens-if-we-pull-on-this kind.

1127
01:29:56,433 --> 01:29:59,311
The learned-it-from-the-Nazis kind.

1128
01:30:01,397 --> 01:30:03,857
That's where they create the ghosts.

1129
01:30:05,275 --> 01:30:09,154
Who knows about this?
On the island, I mean. Who?

1130
01:30:11,490 --> 01:30:12,783
Everyone.

1131
01:30:12,825 --> 01:30:16,537
Come on. The nurses? The orderlies?

1132
01:30:17,121 --> 01:30:20,416
- They couldn't possibly know...
- Everyone.

1133
01:30:39,351 --> 01:30:40,894
You can't stay here.

1134
01:30:41,520 --> 01:30:42,855
They think I'm dead, that I drowned.

1135
01:30:42,896 --> 01:30:45,899
I'm afraid if they come looking for you,
they might find me.

1136
01:30:45,983 --> 01:30:48,360
I'm sorry, but you have to go.

1137
01:30:54,992 --> 01:30:56,618
I'm gonna come back for you.

1138
01:30:56,702 --> 01:30:59,705
I won't be here. I move during the day.
New places every night.

1139
01:30:59,746 --> 01:31:02,082
But I could come get you,
get you off this island.

1140
01:31:02,166 --> 01:31:04,084
Haven't you heard a word I've said?

1141
01:31:04,960 --> 01:31:08,213
The only way off the island is the ferry,
and they control it.

1142
01:31:09,173 --> 01:31:11,216
You'll never leave here.

1143
01:31:20,559 --> 01:31:22,394
I had a friend.

1144
01:31:22,436 --> 01:31:24,938
I was with him yesterday,
but we got separated.

1145
01:31:26,064 --> 01:31:27,733
Have you seen him?

1146
01:31:28,901 --> 01:31:30,235
Marshal,

1147
01:31:31,778 --> 01:31:33,906
you have no friends.

1148
01:32:06,230 --> 01:32:07,773
There you are.

1149
01:32:10,609 --> 01:32:13,278
We were wondering
when you'd show up.

1150
01:32:14,905 --> 01:32:16,448
Have a seat.

1151
01:32:16,907 --> 01:32:18,200
Come on.

1152
01:32:28,877 --> 01:32:31,505
Taking a leisurely stroll, were we?

1153
01:32:32,589 --> 01:32:35,634
I was just looking around.

1154
01:32:38,595 --> 01:32:41,014
Did you enjoy God's latest gift?

1155
01:32:42,641 --> 01:32:43,976
- What?
- God's gift.

1156
01:32:46,144 --> 01:32:47,479
The violence.

1157
01:32:50,315 --> 01:32:54,695
When I came downstairs in my home
and I saw that tree in my living room,

1158
01:32:54,778 --> 01:32:58,615
it reached out for me like a divine hand.

1159
01:33:00,826 --> 01:33:02,661
God loves violence.

1160
01:33:05,330 --> 01:33:08,166
- I hadn't noticed.
- Sure you have.

1161
01:33:09,334 --> 01:33:11,503
Why else would there be so much of it?

1162
01:33:11,837 --> 01:33:13,213
It's in us.

1163
01:33:13,755 --> 01:33:15,090
It's what we are.

1164
01:33:16,508 --> 01:33:18,844
We wage war, we burn sacrifices,

1165
01:33:18,927 --> 01:33:21,513
and pillage and plunder
and tear at the flesh of our brothers.

1166
01:33:21,555 --> 01:33:25,475
And why? Because God gave us
violence to wage in his honor.

1167
01:33:28,687 --> 01:33:31,106
I thought God gave us moral order.

1168
01:33:31,189 --> 01:33:34,192
There's no moral order
as pure as this storm.

1169
01:33:34,818 --> 01:33:38,363
There's no moral order at all.
There's just this,

1170
01:33:38,989 --> 01:33:41,158
can my violence conquer yours?

1171
01:33:46,538 --> 01:33:48,957
- I'm not violent.
- Yes, you are.

1172
01:33:50,083 --> 01:33:52,502
You're as violent as they come.

1173
01:33:53,211 --> 01:33:56,840
I know this
because I'm as violent as they come.

1174
01:33:56,882 --> 01:33:59,051
If the constraints of society were lifted,

1175
01:33:59,134 --> 01:34:01,803
and I was all that stood
between you and a meal,

1176
01:34:01,887 --> 01:34:05,265
you would crack my skull with a rock
and eat my meaty parts.

1177
01:34:07,225 --> 01:34:08,810
Wouldn't you?

1178
01:34:11,563 --> 01:34:14,066
Cawley thinks you're harmless,
that you can be controlled,

1179
01:34:14,107 --> 01:34:15,984
but I know different.

1180
01:34:16,610 --> 01:34:18,403
- You don't know me.
- Oh, but I do.

1181
01:34:18,445 --> 01:34:21,073
- No, you don't. You don't know me at all.
- Oh, I know you.

1182
01:34:21,698 --> 01:34:24,409
We've known each other for centuries.

1183
01:34:33,752 --> 01:34:36,713
If I was to sink my teeth
into your eye right now,

1184
01:34:36,755 --> 01:34:40,092
would you be able to stop me
before I blinded you?

1185
01:34:44,221 --> 01:34:45,847
Give it a try.

1186
01:34:47,391 --> 01:34:49,101
That's the spirit.

1187
01:35:23,844 --> 01:35:27,180
Don't worry, because we're going
to get you back to your room.

1188
01:35:28,098 --> 01:35:29,808
- Not really.
- Something I've seen.

1189
01:35:29,850 --> 01:35:31,101
Okay.

1190
01:35:36,314 --> 01:35:38,066
Where have you been?

1191
01:35:38,150 --> 01:35:40,902
Oh, just wandering.
Just looking at your island.

1192
01:35:40,986 --> 01:35:44,656
Oh, I forgot you're leaving
now that Rachel's been found.

1193
01:35:45,490 --> 01:35:46,950
- Stop looking at him.
- For sure. Yeah.

1194
01:35:46,992 --> 01:35:49,035
Stop looking at him. Stop looking at him.

1195
01:35:50,328 --> 01:35:52,164
- Big meeting?
- Oh, yes.

1196
01:35:52,247 --> 01:35:53,498
- It's okay. I'm...
- I don't like that.

1197
01:35:54,166 --> 01:35:56,168
Apparently there was
an unidentified man

1198
01:35:56,251 --> 01:35:57,544
in Ward C yesterday.

1199
01:35:57,627 --> 01:36:01,006
He subdued a highly dangerous patient
quite handily.

1200
01:36:01,590 --> 01:36:02,591
Is that so?

1201
01:36:02,674 --> 01:36:05,177
It seems he had a long conversation
with a paranoid schizophrenic,

1202
01:36:05,218 --> 01:36:06,428
George Noyce.

1203
01:36:06,511 --> 01:36:09,347
Well, I don't remember
what I'm supposed to remember.

1204
01:36:09,389 --> 01:36:11,141
We're gated down. We're fine.

1205
01:36:11,183 --> 01:36:15,228
This Noyce, you said his name was,
he's delusional?

1206
01:36:15,312 --> 01:36:18,023
Oh, extremely.
He can be quite upsetting.

1207
01:36:18,106 --> 01:36:19,858
As a matter of fact, two weeks ago,

1208
01:36:19,900 --> 01:36:24,362
a patient got so wound up by one
of Noyce's stories that he beat him up.

1209
01:36:25,071 --> 01:36:26,531
- Hmm.
- Cigarette?

1210
01:36:28,825 --> 01:36:30,619
No, thanks. I quit.

1211
01:36:31,703 --> 01:36:35,749
- So you're taking the ferry?
- Yes, absolutely.

1212
01:36:35,832 --> 01:36:38,543
I think we've gotten
all we came here for, so...

1213
01:36:39,377 --> 01:36:40,712
"We," Marshal?

1214
01:36:42,714 --> 01:36:46,301
Speaking of which,
have you seen him, Doctor?

1215
01:36:46,384 --> 01:36:47,552
Who?

1216
01:36:48,386 --> 01:36:50,096
My partner, Chuck.

1217
01:36:52,432 --> 01:36:55,268
You don't have a partner, Marshal.
You came here alone.

1218
01:36:57,729 --> 01:36:59,898
You know, I've built
something valuable here,

1219
01:36:59,981 --> 01:37:03,151
and valuable things have a way of
being misunderstood in their own time.

1220
01:37:03,235 --> 01:37:05,320
Everyone wants a quick fix.
They always have.

1221
01:37:05,403 --> 01:37:09,032
I'm trying to do something that people,
yourself included, don't understand.

1222
01:37:09,074 --> 01:37:12,035
And I'm not going to give up
without a fight.

1223
01:37:13,870 --> 01:37:15,497
I can see that.

1224
01:37:17,415 --> 01:37:18,542
Mmm.

1225
01:37:19,584 --> 01:37:22,212
So, tell me again about your partner.

1226
01:37:23,922 --> 01:37:25,549
What partner?

1227
01:37:28,301 --> 01:37:29,386
It's fine.

1228
01:38:17,726 --> 01:38:21,146
She made a mess.
I cleaned it up. She made a mess again.

1229
01:38:30,822 --> 01:38:32,198
Marshal,

1230
01:38:33,575 --> 01:38:35,201
going somewhere?

1231
01:38:35,493 --> 01:38:38,413
I'm just
heading out to the ferry, so...

1232
01:38:38,496 --> 01:38:42,042
Ah! Oh, well, I'm afraid it's the other way.

1233
01:38:43,585 --> 01:38:44,669
Oh?

1234
01:38:45,670 --> 01:38:50,342
If you'll wait a moment, I'll find you
someone who can take you to the dock.

1235
01:38:55,013 --> 01:38:58,850
- What's this, Doctor? Huh? What's this?
- It's just a sedative.

1236
01:38:58,934 --> 01:39:02,103
- A precaution.
- Oh! A precaution.

1237
01:39:04,314 --> 01:39:07,901
What are you going to do? Kill me?

1238
01:39:08,234 --> 01:39:11,029
- Marshal.
- You think you deserve it?

1239
01:39:11,112 --> 01:39:13,907
For what, hmm? Provoking you?

1240
01:39:14,699 --> 01:39:17,535
Well, forgive me.
What doesn't provoke you?

1241
01:39:18,078 --> 01:39:21,039
- Remarks? Words?
- Nazis?

1242
01:39:21,665 --> 01:39:25,710
Well, that, too.
And, of course, memories, dreams.

1243
01:39:26,795 --> 01:39:31,049
Did you know that the word "trauma"
comes from the Greek for "wound"?

1244
01:39:31,716 --> 01:39:34,469
And what is the German word
for "dream"?

1245
01:39:34,552 --> 01:39:36,721
<i>Traum. Ein Traum.</i>

1246
01:39:38,098 --> 01:39:41,059
Wounds can create monsters,
and you...

1247
01:39:41,726 --> 01:39:44,104
You are wounded, Marshal.

1248
01:39:45,146 --> 01:39:48,316
And wouldn't you agree,
when you see a monster,

1249
01:39:49,025 --> 01:39:50,777
you must stop it?

1250
01:39:51,361 --> 01:39:52,570
Yeah.

1251
01:39:53,738 --> 01:39:55,573
- I agree.
- Yes.

1252
01:39:56,408 --> 01:39:57,492
Yeah.

1253
01:40:14,718 --> 01:40:16,970
I told him that we'd take
about an hour to do it.

1254
01:40:17,053 --> 01:40:20,140
Yeah. Did they say
we're going to do the first floor?

1255
01:40:20,223 --> 01:40:21,474
How long
you been the clock?

1256
01:40:21,558 --> 01:40:23,935
I've been on
for 18 hours straight.

1257
01:40:24,394 --> 01:40:25,937
Nice paycheck.

1258
01:40:42,412 --> 01:40:44,497
What are you doing, baby?

1259
01:40:49,294 --> 01:40:51,796
- You gotta get to the ferry.
- No.

1260
01:40:52,547 --> 01:40:53,840
No, no.

1261
01:40:55,050 --> 01:40:56,217
Yeah.

1262
01:40:57,343 --> 01:41:02,223
If the world thinks that Chuck is dead,
then he's perfect for their experiments.

1263
01:41:03,308 --> 01:41:05,560
There's only one place they'd take him.

1264
01:41:08,188 --> 01:41:10,732
- You go there and you'll die.
- He's my partner.

1265
01:41:10,815 --> 01:41:12,901
If they are hurting him,
if they're holding him against his will,

1266
01:41:12,984 --> 01:41:14,694
I've gotta bring him out.

1267
01:41:14,903 --> 01:41:16,988
I can't lose anyone else.

1268
01:41:17,030 --> 01:41:18,323
Don't go, Teddy, please.

1269
01:41:18,364 --> 01:41:21,785
- Please, don't do this. Don't go.
- I'm sorry, honey.

1270
01:41:25,371 --> 01:41:27,165
I'm sorry, honey.

1271
01:41:28,249 --> 01:41:31,294
I love this thing
because you gave it to me,

1272
01:41:33,671 --> 01:41:35,507
but the truth is

1273
01:41:37,175 --> 01:41:39,344
it is one fucking ugly tie.

1274
01:42:19,551 --> 01:42:20,718
No.

1275
01:43:42,634 --> 01:43:44,010
Don't move. Stay where you are.

1276
01:43:46,012 --> 01:43:47,430
Are you gonna kill me?

1277
01:43:49,098 --> 01:43:51,643
No, I'm not gonna kill you.

1278
01:45:44,255 --> 01:45:46,132
Why are you all wet, baby?

1279
01:45:48,343 --> 01:45:51,596
- What did you say?
- You know exactly what I said.

1280
01:46:04,692 --> 01:46:06,944
The rifle's empty, by the way.

1281
01:46:13,451 --> 01:46:14,952
Have a seat.

1282
01:46:21,459 --> 01:46:23,878
For God's sake, dry off.
You'll catch cold.

1283
01:46:25,505 --> 01:46:26,631
All right.

1284
01:46:30,176 --> 01:46:32,095
How badly did you hurt the guard?

1285
01:46:33,805 --> 01:46:36,808
I don't know
what you're talking about.

1286
01:46:39,977 --> 01:46:41,938
Yes, he's here.

1287
01:46:41,979 --> 01:46:45,983
Have Dr. Sheehan take a look
at your man before you send him up.

1288
01:46:46,067 --> 01:46:50,780
So Dr. Sheehan came in on the ferry
this morning, huh?

1289
01:46:51,739 --> 01:46:53,241
Not exactly.

1290
01:46:54,283 --> 01:46:57,328
You blew up my car.
I really loved that car.

1291
01:46:58,246 --> 01:47:00,331
Sorry to hear about that.

1292
01:47:03,626 --> 01:47:06,003
Tremors are getting pretty bad.

1293
01:47:06,629 --> 01:47:09,048
How are the hallucinations?

1294
01:47:09,132 --> 01:47:13,302
Get out of here, Teddy.
This place is gonna be the end of you.

1295
01:47:17,056 --> 01:47:18,182
Not bad.

1296
01:47:18,266 --> 01:47:20,852
- They'll get worse.
- I know.

1297
01:47:21,727 --> 01:47:26,023
Dr. Solando,
she told me about the neuroleptics.

1298
01:47:26,566 --> 01:47:29,026
Did she, now? And when was this?

1299
01:47:29,110 --> 01:47:33,906
I found her, Doctor,
in a cave out by the cliffs.

1300
01:47:33,990 --> 01:47:36,534
- But you'll never get to her.
- I don't doubt it,

1301
01:47:37,493 --> 01:47:39,162
considering she's not real.

1302
01:47:41,080 --> 01:47:44,208
Your delusions are more severe
than I thought.

1303
01:47:45,418 --> 01:47:47,587
You're not on neuroleptics.

1304
01:47:48,045 --> 01:47:49,922
You're not on anything,
as a matter of fact.

1305
01:47:50,006 --> 01:47:52,633
Then what the fuck is this? Huh?
What the fuck is this?

1306
01:47:52,717 --> 01:47:53,718
Withdrawal.

1307
01:47:54,719 --> 01:47:56,721
Withdrawal? From what?

1308
01:47:56,762 --> 01:47:59,098
I haven't had a goddamn drink
since I've been on this island.

1309
01:47:59,182 --> 01:48:00,808
Chlorpromazine.

1310
01:48:01,642 --> 01:48:04,896
I'm not a fan of pharmacology,
but I have to say, in your case...

1311
01:48:05,396 --> 01:48:08,649
- Chloraproma-what?
- Chlorpromazine.

1312
01:48:08,733 --> 01:48:12,737
The same thing we've been giving you
for the past 24 months.

1313
01:48:14,030 --> 01:48:16,157
Oh, so for the past two years, you...

1314
01:48:16,240 --> 01:48:19,577
You've had somebody slipping me drugs
in Boston. Is that it?

1315
01:48:19,619 --> 01:48:21,078
Not Boston.

1316
01:48:21,579 --> 01:48:22,747
Here.

1317
01:48:23,539 --> 01:48:27,502
You've been here for two years.
A patient of this institution.

1318
01:48:31,255 --> 01:48:33,424
After everything I've seen here, Doctor,

1319
01:48:35,092 --> 01:48:38,513
you really think you're gonna
convince me I'm crazy, huh?

1320
01:48:38,596 --> 01:48:40,598
Do you know the kind of people
that I deal with every day?

1321
01:48:40,640 --> 01:48:42,517
I'm a U.S. Marshal, for God's sakes.

1322
01:48:42,600 --> 01:48:44,477
You were a U.S. Marshal.

1323
01:48:44,560 --> 01:48:48,356
Here's a copy of the intake form
you broke into Ward C for.

1324
01:48:48,439 --> 01:48:49,815
Proof of the 67th patient.

1325
01:48:49,899 --> 01:48:51,108
If you'd gotten it to the mainland,

1326
01:48:51,150 --> 01:48:52,944
you could have blown the lid
off this place.

1327
01:48:53,027 --> 01:48:54,445
- Wait. Where did... Where did you...
- Yet somehow,

1328
01:48:54,487 --> 01:48:57,406
you couldn't find time to look at it.
Well, read it now.

1329
01:48:58,282 --> 01:48:59,659
Go ahead.

1330
01:49:03,454 --> 01:49:07,291
"Patient is highly intelligent, highly
delusional decorated Army veteran.

1331
01:49:07,375 --> 01:49:09,961
"Present
for the liberation of Dachau.

1332
01:49:11,212 --> 01:49:13,839
"Former U.S. Marshal.
Known proclivity for violence.

1333
01:49:13,923 --> 01:49:17,176
"Shows no remorse for his crime
because he denies the crime ever...

1334
01:49:17,260 --> 01:49:18,302
"Ever took place.

1335
01:49:18,386 --> 01:49:20,304
"Highly developed
and fantastical narratives,

1336
01:49:20,346 --> 01:49:22,723
"which preclude
facing the truth of his actions."

1337
01:49:22,807 --> 01:49:25,476
I've had enough of this bullshit!
Where's my partner, huh?

1338
01:49:25,560 --> 01:49:27,144
Where's Chuck? Where is he?

1339
01:49:27,937 --> 01:49:29,647
Let's try this another way.

1340
01:49:29,730 --> 01:49:32,316
Your wife's maiden name was Chanal,
am I correct?

1341
01:49:32,358 --> 01:49:33,818
Don't you even talk about her.
Don't you...

1342
01:49:33,859 --> 01:49:35,736
I'm afraid I have to.

1343
01:49:37,780 --> 01:49:39,949
Notice anything
these four names have in common?

1344
01:49:40,157 --> 01:49:41,659
It's your rule of four.

1345
01:49:42,118 --> 01:49:43,286
Andrew, what do you see?

1346
01:49:43,327 --> 01:49:46,330
If you've done anything to my partner,
Doctor, that is a violation of...

1347
01:49:46,414 --> 01:49:48,833
Focus, Andrew! What do you see?

1348
01:49:49,834 --> 01:49:52,336
The names have the same letters.

1349
01:49:53,212 --> 01:49:56,674
Edward Daniels has exactly
the same 13 letters as Andrew Laeddis.

1350
01:49:56,716 --> 01:49:58,968
The same as Rachel Solando
and Dolores Chanal.

1351
01:49:59,010 --> 01:50:01,095
The names are anagrams
for each other.

1352
01:50:01,178 --> 01:50:03,764
Your tactics,
they're not gonna work on me.

1353
01:50:03,848 --> 01:50:06,684
You came here for the truth. Here it is.

1354
01:50:06,726 --> 01:50:08,728
Your name is Andrew Laeddis.

1355
01:50:08,811 --> 01:50:12,356
The 67th patient at Ashecliffe
is you, Andrew.

1356
01:50:14,191 --> 01:50:15,192
Bullshit.

1357
01:50:15,234 --> 01:50:17,445
You were committed here by court order
24 months ago.

1358
01:50:17,528 --> 01:50:20,865
Your crime is terrible,
one you can't forgive yourself for,

1359
01:50:20,948 --> 01:50:23,326
so you invented another self.

1360
01:50:25,494 --> 01:50:26,912
All right.

1361
01:50:27,413 --> 01:50:30,082
Let's get down
to the facts, all right?

1362
01:50:30,166 --> 01:50:33,044
You've created a story
in which you're not a murderer.

1363
01:50:33,127 --> 01:50:37,214
You're a hero, still a U.S. Marshal, only
here at Ashecliffe because of a case,

1364
01:50:37,256 --> 01:50:38,758
and you've uncovered a conspiracy

1365
01:50:38,841 --> 01:50:42,386
so that anything we tell you
about who you are, what you've done,

1366
01:50:42,470 --> 01:50:44,555
you can dismiss as lies, Andrew.

1367
01:50:44,597 --> 01:50:45,890
My name is Edward Daniels.

1368
01:50:45,973 --> 01:50:50,227
I've been hearing this fantasy
for two years now. I know every detail.

1369
01:50:50,311 --> 01:50:52,271
Patient 67, the storm,

1370
01:50:52,355 --> 01:50:55,566
Rachel Solando, your missing partner,
the dreams you have every night.

1371
01:50:55,650 --> 01:50:58,069
You were at Dachau,
but you may not have killed any guards.

1372
01:51:02,114 --> 01:51:05,785
I wish I could let you
just live in your fantasy world.

1373
01:51:05,868 --> 01:51:07,328
I really do.

1374
01:51:08,204 --> 01:51:10,414
But you're violent, trained, dangerous.

1375
01:51:10,498 --> 01:51:12,792
You're the most dangerous patient
we have.

1376
01:51:12,875 --> 01:51:15,169
You've injured orderlies, guards,
other patients.

1377
01:51:15,252 --> 01:51:17,213
Two weeks ago,
you attacked George Noyce.

1378
01:51:17,254 --> 01:51:19,548
No, no. I am fucking on to you, Doctor.

1379
01:51:19,590 --> 01:51:21,467
- You had Noyce beaten.
- Of course I didn't!

1380
01:51:21,550 --> 01:51:23,636
Give me one reason
why I would even touch him!

1381
01:51:23,719 --> 01:51:26,097
Because he called you Laeddis,

1382
01:51:26,180 --> 01:51:29,266
and you'd do anything not to be him.

1383
01:51:29,308 --> 01:51:32,937
I have a transcript of the conversation
you had with Noyce yesterday.

1384
01:51:32,978 --> 01:51:37,024
"This is about you, and, Laeddis,
that's all it's ever been about."

1385
01:51:38,943 --> 01:51:41,445
No, no. He's saying
this is about me and Laeddis.

1386
01:51:41,529 --> 01:51:43,447
When you asked him
what happened to his face,

1387
01:51:43,489 --> 01:51:46,909
he said, now here I'm quoting again,
"You did this."

1388
01:51:46,951 --> 01:51:49,120
No, no, he meant that it was my fault.

1389
01:51:49,161 --> 01:51:51,163
You almost killed him.

1390
01:51:52,832 --> 01:51:55,626
The warden and the Board of Overseers
are determined something be done.

1391
01:51:55,710 --> 01:51:57,461
It's been decided

1392
01:51:57,503 --> 01:52:00,339
that unless we can bring you
back to sanity now,

1393
01:52:00,631 --> 01:52:01,924
right now,

1394
01:52:02,216 --> 01:52:05,636
permanent measures will be taken to
ensure you can't hurt anyone ever again.

1395
01:52:09,140 --> 01:52:12,476
They'll lobotomize you, Andrew.
Do you understand?

1396
01:52:16,731 --> 01:52:18,649
Yeah, I understand.

1397
01:52:19,483 --> 01:52:21,694
I understand just fine.

1398
01:52:22,319 --> 01:52:26,407
If I don't play along
with your little game here,

1399
01:52:26,490 --> 01:52:29,618
Dr. Naehring's gonna turn me
into one of his ghosts.

1400
01:52:30,077 --> 01:52:31,495
But what about my partner?

1401
01:52:31,537 --> 01:52:36,000
You gonna tell the U.S. Marshal's office
that he's a defense mechanism?

1402
01:52:37,877 --> 01:52:39,336
Hello, boss.

1403
01:52:56,187 --> 01:52:59,356
What the fuck
is going on here? Hmm?

1404
01:53:00,441 --> 01:53:01,525
Huh?

1405
01:53:01,859 --> 01:53:05,488
You working for him?

1406
01:53:06,322 --> 01:53:07,865
I'm sorry. There wasn't any other way.

1407
01:53:07,907 --> 01:53:10,826
Someone had to stick with you,
keep you safe.

1408
01:53:13,704 --> 01:53:15,831
You been watching me, huh?

1409
01:53:16,791 --> 01:53:18,876
Watching me every minute.

1410
01:53:19,794 --> 01:53:21,086
Who are you?

1411
01:53:21,837 --> 01:53:22,922
Who are you? Tell me.

1412
01:53:23,589 --> 01:53:25,591
Don't you recognize me, Andrew?

1413
01:53:27,009 --> 01:53:30,721
I've been your primary psychiatrist
for the last two years.

1414
01:53:31,305 --> 01:53:33,182
I'm Lester Sheehan.

1415
01:53:39,647 --> 01:53:42,316
- I told you... I told you about my wife, I...
- I know.

1416
01:53:42,399 --> 01:53:45,653
I climbed down a cliff to get you.
I trusted you.

1417
01:53:45,736 --> 01:53:49,406
I risked everything to come in here
after you. Everything!

1418
01:53:49,448 --> 01:53:52,201
- I know, boss.
- We're running out of time here, Andrew.

1419
01:53:53,744 --> 01:53:55,329
I swore before the Board of Overseers

1420
01:53:55,412 --> 01:53:59,333
that I could construct the most radical,
cutting-edge role-play

1421
01:53:59,416 --> 01:54:01,710
ever attempted in psychiatry,
and it would bring you back.

1422
01:54:01,752 --> 01:54:04,129
I thought that if we let you play this out

1423
01:54:04,880 --> 01:54:08,509
we could get you to see how untrue,
how impossible it is.

1424
01:54:09,593 --> 01:54:12,096
You've had the run of the place
for two days.

1425
01:54:12,137 --> 01:54:15,432
Tell me, where are
the Nazi experiments?

1426
01:54:15,516 --> 01:54:17,309
The satanic ORs?

1427
01:54:30,948 --> 01:54:34,493
Andrew, listen to me.

1428
01:54:35,202 --> 01:54:36,787
If we fail with you,

1429
01:54:37,538 --> 01:54:41,458
then everything that we've tried to do
here will be discredited. Everything.

1430
01:54:43,586 --> 01:54:46,755
We're on the front lines of a war
here, old boy.

1431
01:54:47,506 --> 01:54:50,384
And right now, it all comes down to you.

1432
01:54:57,308 --> 01:55:00,019
- Don't move! Don't move!
- Andrew! Andrew! No. No.

1433
01:55:00,102 --> 01:55:03,314
My name
is Edward Daniels!

1434
01:55:03,397 --> 01:55:05,482
This one's loaded.
I can tell by the weight.

1435
01:55:05,524 --> 01:55:08,152
I see. And that's your firearm, Marshal?
You're sure?

1436
01:55:08,193 --> 01:55:09,403
My initials are on the side.

1437
01:55:09,486 --> 01:55:11,822
There's a dent in the barrel
from when Philip Stacks shot at me.

1438
01:55:11,864 --> 01:55:13,991
You're not gonna fuck with my mind
on this one, Doctor!

1439
01:55:14,074 --> 01:55:15,159
Then blast away.

1440
01:55:15,200 --> 01:55:18,537
Because that's the only way
you're ever getting off this island.

1441
01:55:24,627 --> 01:55:26,503
Andrew, please don't.

1442
01:55:37,389 --> 01:55:38,682
My gun.

1443
01:55:45,272 --> 01:55:47,858
What did you do to my goddamn gun?

1444
01:55:48,275 --> 01:55:50,444
It's a toy, Andrew.

1445
01:55:52,947 --> 01:55:55,032
We're telling you the truth.

1446
01:55:55,532 --> 01:55:58,786
Dolores was insane,
manic-depressive, suicidal.

1447
01:55:59,453 --> 01:56:02,539
You drank, stayed away,
ignored what everyone told you.

1448
01:56:02,623 --> 01:56:03,749
You moved to that lake house

1449
01:56:03,832 --> 01:56:07,002
after she purposely set
your city apartment on fire.

1450
01:56:07,044 --> 01:56:08,379
- You were...
- You're lying!

1451
01:56:08,420 --> 01:56:11,882
- Andrew! Andrew, stop. No.
- You drugged the cigarettes!

1452
01:56:11,966 --> 01:56:13,842
- All you've done is lie!
- Andrew. Andrew.

1453
01:56:13,884 --> 01:56:16,428
Your children. Andrew, your children.

1454
01:56:17,179 --> 01:56:19,848
Simon. Henry.

1455
01:56:20,224 --> 01:56:21,558
I never had any children.

1456
01:56:21,600 --> 01:56:25,646
Your wife drowned them
at the cabin by the lake.

1457
01:56:25,729 --> 01:56:28,941
And here, the little girl,
the one you dream of

1458
01:56:29,650 --> 01:56:31,318
every night.

1459
01:56:31,402 --> 01:56:32,569
I never had a little girl.

1460
01:56:32,653 --> 01:56:36,240
The one who tells you over and over
that you should have saved her,

1461
01:56:36,323 --> 01:56:38,242
saved them all.

1462
01:56:38,325 --> 01:56:40,786
Your daughter, her name was Rachel.

1463
01:56:40,869 --> 01:56:43,747
Are you going to deny
that she ever lived?

1464
01:56:44,498 --> 01:56:46,250
Andrew, are you?

1465
01:57:09,231 --> 01:57:11,316
I'm so sorry, baby.

1466
01:57:15,696 --> 01:57:18,073
I told you not to come in here.

1467
01:57:18,532 --> 01:57:22,494
I told you this would be the end of you.

1468
01:57:42,848 --> 01:57:44,183
I'm back!

1469
01:57:44,808 --> 01:57:47,561
We got him just outside of Oklahoma.

1470
01:57:47,644 --> 01:57:50,189
Must've stopped 10 places
in between here and Tulsa.

1471
01:57:50,272 --> 01:57:52,357
I could sleep for a week.

